            <h3>2.7. Avoid exposure to high temperatures and humidity</h3>
            <p class="text-indent">Silver jewelry should be stored in a low-humidity environment with stable temperatures. Avoid storing silver jewelry in high-humidity places or exposing them to high temperatures. If you do not use silver jewelry for a long time, store them in an air-tight bag or box made of dry material to prevent them from oxidizing.</p>
            <img src="./icon_wed/bq07.jpg" alt="">
            <h5>Avoid exposing jewelry to high temperatures</h5>
            <h3>2.8. Use paper or soft fabric bags for storage and cleaning</h3>
            <p class="text-indent">Avoid using plastic bags or other wrapping materials to store your silver jewelry. These materials can damage the silver and cause it to oxidize quickly. Instead, use paper or fabric bags to store your silver jewelry. Paper and fabric bags will keep your jewelry dry and free from moisture, helping to prevent silver jewelry from oxidizing.</p>
